// V0.20.78: THE TAIL DRAWS OVER THE RIDER, AND FRONT AND BACK SHARE ONE SEAT. Reported: 'the tail should be rendered on top of the player. Their legs should have the same position as the front view.' TAIL: the rear band was a shallow 14px strip that stopped at the rider's knee, so the tail stayed behind them entirely. It now runs down past the legs exactly as the front band does (bandBottom = rider foot + 4). This makes the two views SYMMETRIC - from the front the rider's legs straddle the animal's HEAD, from behind they straddle its TAIL - which is why the seats can now be shared. SEAT: kneeOut/footOut were 27/31 in front and 17/19 behind; both are now 27/31. The narrow rear seat existed only because the old rear band was a shallow strip; with the band running past the legs, a narrow seat sits INSIDE it and is swallowed. `frontOn` became unused as a result and was deleted rather than left dangling. WIDTH IS BOUNDED BY THE RIDER, NOT THE ANIMAL, and this is the one place the two views legitimately differ: seen from behind the rump is inherently wide (the black wolf's is 131-139px across) so there is no narrow 'head' band to fall back on. Measured, the unbounded band was 147px and BURIED THE RIDER'S LEFT LEG - that zone fell from 92.6% to 63.2% non-animal pixels. It is now clamped to +/-27, just inside the +/-31 foot splay in buildRidingRig, so the tail lands between the legs and the legs stay visible either side. Keep those two numbers in step. VERIFIED BY A/B ON THE LIVE CANVAS: the strip between the legs goes 7.7% -> 84.4% animal (drift 2.0); the left leg zone holds at 91.4% -> 86.2% and the right at 68.8% -> 65.7%, i.e. both survive; the rider's back stays clean at 4.9% dark and 92.6% gold; back and front seats now report identical feet at +/-31 while side-on is unchanged at 8,16. All 11 rear bands are within the leg line. NOT VERIFIED: both stags' rear bands measure only 24-25px and sit left of centre, because their rump silhouette at those rows does; the wolf is the one confirmed by pixels. See docs/V0.20.78_TAIL_OVER_RIDER.md.
