// V0.20.77: FRONT VIEW - THE RIDER'S LOWER BODY GOES BEHIND THE MOUNT'S HEAD AND UPPER BODY. Reported: 'the lower body should be hidden behind the mounts head and upper body'. MEASURED FIRST, via an ASCII colour map of the live canvas: the rider's lower body is a solid white block at dy -58..-31 (hip -51, foot -26) and the overlay band ended at -53 - precisely where that block begins, which is why it was fully visible. FIX: facing the camera the band now runs from the head down past the rider's legs (bandBottom = rider foot + 4), so the animal's head AND chest do the occluding. Extending is safe by construction: the band only clips a REDRAW OF THE MOUNT, so it can paint the animal's own chest and can never reveal background. WIDTH IS TAKEN FROM THE HEAD AND CHEST ROWS ONLY, not the whole band: sampling the full band swept in the angled flank (the black wolf jumps from 81px wide at dy -56 to 142px at -53) and produced a 152px box that buried the rider's legs too - the very thing V0.20.72 splayed them to +/-31 to avoid. Head+withers rows give 90px. A CLAMP AGAINST THE HEAD SPAN WAS BUILT AND THEN REMOVED: it was measurably INERT, producing byte-identical widths on all 11 mounts, so it was dead complexity of exactly the kind deleted in V0.20.75. KNOWN AND DELIBERATELY NOT TOUCHED: the boars get much wider front boxes (briar boar 141px, old tusk 202px) because the shoulder detection NEVER FIRES for them - their skull merges straight into the shoulders so headWidth*1.9 is a threshold the silhouette never crosses (old tusk: probe 106, threshold 201, actual max 182) and shoulderY falls back to 42% of height. That is PRE-EXISTING, not introduced here, and for a boar covering that width may well be right since the rider's legs sit behind its bulk anyway; it needs eyes on a boar mount before being changed. VERIFIED BY A/B ON THE LIVE CANVAS: rider lower body 59.0% -> 0.7% white with the overlay on (drift 0.0); rider UPPER body 36.6% -> 33.8%, i.e. untouched; the rider's right foot survives (13.7% -> 13.0%). See docs/V0.20.77_FRONT_LOWER_BODY_BEHIND_MOUNT.md.
