// V0.20.76: THE OVERLAY IS MEASURED AT THE FACING IT IS ACTUALLY DRAWN AT - closing a bug class hit four times. Reported: front view still has a slight clipping issue; back view still shows the head; side view still shows the whole chest and both arms. ROOT CAUSE (front): mountOverlayBox probed the beast at a CANNED facing (straight south for front, straight north for rear) while the game draws DIAGONALS. Measured on the black wolf: probe 'south' puts the head centre at dx -11 and 64px wide; the drawn 'southeast' puts it at dx +33 and 43px wide - the clip rect sat 44px to the LEFT of the real head, so it cut one side of the head off and redrew blank canvas over the rider's chest. FIX: mountOverlayBox now takes the entity's real facing (mountProbeFacing) and caches per quantised heading, so the box always describes the silhouette that reaches the screen. This is the SAME probe-vs-draw mismatch as V0.20.65 (animal facing), V0.20.69 (riding pose reaching the model) and V0.20.73 (which seat the rider adopts) - fourth occurrence, now fixed at the measurement instead of per-symptom. CONSEQUENCE: the x1.55 head-height multiplier from V0.20.74 is REMOVED. It existed only to reach a muzzle the mis-aimed box appeared to be cutting off; with correct measurement it was pure over-reach, running the box to -39 against a head ending at -61 and repainting the animal's neck across the rider's thighs - which was the reported 'slight clipping'. Box is now the measured head plus a 9px jaw pad: -86..-53 against a head at -83..-61. SIDE VIEW: buildRidingRig kept shoulderW/hipW at FULL breadth side-on. V0.20.74 moved both HANDS to the near side but the chest still read face-on with an arm on each edge. Shoulder and hip spans now compress to 0.46 side-on (span 7.6-11.5 vs 22 front, i.e. 35-52%), which is what actually turns the body into a profile and tucks the far arm behind the near one. The standing rig always did this via its own sideCompress; the riding rig never did. MEASUREMENT NOTE: this is the first version whose render claims are backed by REAL PIXELS. Sampling had failed silently since V0.20.71 because the world camera transform is applied to the CONTEXT - foot (670,633) maps to canvas (482,456) under a=d=0.9216, e=-135.07, f=-127.61 - so every window aimed with worldToScreen() or with the raw foot argument missed the character by ~190px and returned near-zero with the change both ON and OFF. Wrapping the draw call to capture ctx.getTransform() fixed it. VERIFIED BY A/B ON THE LIVE CANVAS: front overlay adds +43.4% black inside the head zone and only +2.6/+1.7 above it and below it (both within measured drift); true back heading reads 5.6% black and 90.9% gold in the rider's torso band - no head. See docs/V0.20.76_OVERLAY_AT_DRAWN_FACING.md.
