// V0.20.75: REAR OVERLAY ANCHORS TO THE BACK LINE, NOT THE TOP OF THE SILHOUETTE. Reported: from behind, the black wolf's head renders across the rider's back. ROOT CAUSE: mountOverlayBox's rear branch measured a band downward from `top`, the topmost row of the silhouette, on the assumption that from behind the near mass is the rump. It is not - the TOPMOST MASS IS THE HEAD FROM EVERY ANGLE, including from behind. Measured rear profile, black wolf: dy -84..-52 is 21-44px wide (the skull), then -48 jumps to 71px (the shoulders/back), widest 89px at +8 (the haunches). The box covered -90..-49, which is the head almost exactly. FIX: anchor to the BACK LINE - the first row where the outline widens to maxW*0.6 - so the band can never start on the skull or neck. TWO WRONG TURNS TAKEN AND DISCARDED ON EVIDENCE, both caught by measuring rather than reasoning. (1) Anchoring to the SADDLE height instead: rejected because the saddle is measured from a SIDE view, and at that height a REAR silhouette is still neck and skull - it produced a box at -64..-40 against a head at -84..-52, reintroducing the reported bug. (2) Restricting the body-width measurement to the LOWER HALF to keep antlers from skewing maxW: I claimed this was what fixed the stags, then tested it and it is NOT - bodyMax and wholeMax select the SAME anchor row on all 11 mounts (stag antlers are not wider than its ribcage in a rear silhouette). The dead complexity and the comment asserting it were both removed. What actually corrects the stags and arachnids is the PELVIS CLAMP: on both stags and all three arachnids the back line sits ABOVE the rider's pelvis, so the band landed across their CHEST - the wrong half of the body. backY is clamped to the saddle lift so the overlay can only ever lap the lower body. Band depth is 14px: the rider's foot sits only ~20px below the back line, and the report said the legs already looked right, so the haunch laps thigh and knee while the shin and foot stay clear. A null guard was added for the case where the band catches no pixels, so a garbage clip rect can never be used. VERIFIED ACROSS ALL 11 MOUNTS: every box starts at or below the back line, contains real body pixels, laps hip-to-knee, spares the foot and spares the chest. NEGATIVE CONTROL: re-injecting the old top-anchored rule FAILS the check (wolf -89 and stag -133 both above their back lines), so the check has teeth. See docs/V0.20.75_REAR_OVERLAY_BACK_LINE.md.
