// V0.20.47: TWO REQUESTED FIXES - half walk speed, and the FPS counter back. (1) WALK SPEED: added CONFIG.PLAYER_WALK_SPEED_SCALE (0.5) and a single Game.playerWalkSpeed() that every movement path now reads - keyboard (game.js), click-to-move (game.js) and controller (steam-deck-system.js) - so they can never drift apart. Deliberately NOT applied to the speed STAT: the character sheet, gear bonuses and speed buffs all keep reading the real value, so no itemisation or buff maths changes; only the ground covered per second halves. The click-to-move path also had a hardcoded Math.max(0.8, ...) floor which would have silently cancelled the slowdown for anyone at or below it, so the floor scales with the knob too. VERIFIED through the real movement call (tryMoveActorSubstepped): 4.55 -> 2.275 tiles/sec, ratio exactly 0.500, speed stat unchanged. (2) FPS COUNTER: the logic was never gone - updateFpsCounter() has been computing a real presentation-cadence FPS (500ms window, EMA-smoothed) and calling it every frame all along, but V0.17.06 removed it from the Mini-Map HUD and the #fpsCounter element went with it, so it was writing into nothing. Restored the element (with the .fpsValue span the code looks for) plus styling, under the mini-map, hidden until the game starts like the rest of the HUD. VERIFIED by driving the REAL updater: simulated 60fps renders '60 FPS', simulated 20fps renders '20 FPS'. Note the updater intentionally bails when document.hidden - correct behaviour, and the reason it reads 0 inside a non-presenting browser pane. Suite ok, 396/396, 0 console errors. See docs/V0.20.47_WALK_SPEED_AND_FPS.md.
