// V0.20.46: PERFORMANCE - THE UPDATE LOOP, ~5x FASTER, WITH NO CONTENT REMOVED. Reported symptom: everything laggy. Profiled rather than guessed, and the first guess (my own V0.20.45 NPC animation work) was WRONG - measured at 7.8ms of a 53.8ms update. Attribution by selective stubbing: the 444 overworld enemies cost 49.3ms of 53.8ms, and within that the single largest item was game.hasStatusTag() at 26.9ms/frame. ROOT CAUSE: StatusEffects.hasTag guarded with Array.isArray(entity.buffs) but never checked LENGTH, so for every entity with an empty buffs array it still ran slug() - two regex replaces plus string allocations - and then .some() over nothing. Live measurement: 517 hasTag calls per frame, 100% of them against an empty buffs array (all 424 enemies carry a buffs array, none had a single buff). FIXES, all behaviour-preserving: (1) hasTag / hasCurableTag / statusSpeedScalar early-out when buffs is empty, before slug; (2) slug() memoised (bounded to 512 entries) because it is called with a tiny fixed vocabulary of constant literals hundreds of times a frame; (3) my own V0.20.44 NPC neighbour scan replaced its O(n^2) hypot storm with an axis reject + squared-distance compare. RESULT: update 53.8ms -> 13.3ms (~5x), hasStatusTag 26.9 -> 2.3ms, updatePatrol 15.6 -> 5.4ms, enemy update 30.2 -> 4.3ms, my NPC system 7.8ms -> ~0. Every enemy, NPC and prop is still there. CORRECTNESS: 10 status-effect assertions pass including the positives - a tagged buff is still found, 'Frost Bite' still normalises to frost_bite, expired buffs still excluded, isCurable still respected, root still zeroes speed. Suite ok, 396/396, 0 console errors. HONEST LIMIT: render is now the dominant half (~44ms) and I do NOT trust my render numbers - the Browser pane page is permanently document.hidden, so it never composites and requestAnimationFrame is throttled to zero, which is also why my earlier FPS claims were unearned. Real-world FPS must be re-measured in-game. See docs/V0.20.46_PERFORMANCE_UPDATE_LOOP.md.
