// V0.20.45: THE CAMP FOLK ACTUALLY WALK - the render-bridge fix that V0.20.44 needed. V0.20.44 made camp NPCs move and set everything a walk animation needs (moveBlend, walkCycle, facingX/facingY), and I verified those FIELDS and called it done. The user reported they still just teleported around with no walking animation - and they were right. Verifying the node state was verifying a PROXY; two places in the render threw that state away before anything could use it. (1) npc-system classActor was built with HARDCODED `facingX: 0, facingY: 1, isMoving: false, action: 'idle'` - so the model and the runtime sprite cache were always told 'standing still, facing south' regardless of what the NPC was doing. (2) drawNpcClassModelDirect then did an unconditional `actor.isMoving = false` one line before the draw, clobbering it again. Because the sprite cache keys its animation bucket off action/isMoving (actionFrameMs + animationBucket), every camp NPC baked as IDLE - 2 buckets at 250ms, effectively one frozen frame - and then slid around wearing it. FIX: derive all four from the live node (moveBlend > 0.08 -> action 'walk' + isMoving true; facingX/facingY passed through; facingName derived from the movement vector via an 8-way mapping, since faceNodeToward only writes the vector). PROVEN AT THE BRIDGE, not on the node: a forced render frame with walkers mid-stride shows 21 of 22 NPC model draws arriving as action 'walk' / isMoving true with facings northwest, north, south, southeast (previously all 'idle'/false/'south'), while a genuinely idle NPC still arrives 'idle'/false. Cache frame math confirms walk yields 5 distinct frames per 600ms vs idle's 2. Also learned: heavy monkey-patching of hot render paths hangs the renderer, and an idle background tab throttles rAF - both produced misleading zero-counts mid-diagnosis. See docs/V0.20.45_NPC_WALK_ANIMATION_FIX.md.
