// V0.20.44: CAMP COMES TO LIFE - camp NPC ambient animation + day/night schedule (Roadmap Item 16 territory), from a side request. The camp had 28 NPCs of which only 2 ever moved (authored patrol), in a radius-2 clockwork orbit, and even those read as a frozen pose SLIDING because moveBlend was set but the render never sustained it. Now every overworld camp NPC has ambient life on top of the walk/idle the atlas already supports (getEntityAtlasAction keys 'walk' off moveBlend>0.08). BY DAY the camp bustles: a home-anchored two-state stroll (walk to a point near the post, pause a beat, pick another), essential NPCs (quest/trainer/vendor) on a tighter leash so they stay findable, ambient folk roaming wider. AT NIGHT almost everyone walks to the nearest tent and sleeps - _asleep nodes are skipped by the renderer, the interaction pickers (findNearbyNpc/findNpcAtWorld) and the minimap; the ethereal dream spirit keeps its vigil. At dawn they wake and return to their posts. THE KEY FIX for the 'teleport' look: moveBlend is now the NPC's walking INTENT (set from state), not per-frame step success - so a blocked frame in the dense camp keeps the gait instead of dropping to idle, which is exactly why the walk animation never engaged before (verified: day walkers went 0/180 frames -> 120/120). Item 16 safety kept: bounded to the AUTHORED home post (save-safe, no drift), isWalkable-gated, no NPC-on-NPC or NPC-on-player overlap, holds still while being talked to, all state runtime (re-derives sleep from the world clock on reload). Verified LIVE through the real game loop: at deep night 26/27 camp NPCs slept in tents (only the Spirit Healer up), 0 on blocked tiles, 0 console errors. The still-visible figures at night are autonomous adventurer BOTS - a separate population, correctly unaffected. See docs/V0.20.44_CAMP_COMES_TO_LIFE.md.
