// V0.20.43: DEAD LANTERN CAMP - Roadmap Item 2, COMPLETED (last residual). Investigation first, and it corrected me: Item 2 was ALREADY substantially built in V0.20.8 (ensureStartingCampRevamp) - my initial prop count was low because I grepped the micro-landmarks function, not the camp-revamp one. Verified LIVE, the camp is rich and correct: 42 objects across 24 types (7 tents + lean-to, cooking area, quartermaster supply line, training area, medical, study, sleeping quarters, torches, banner, clutter), placed deliberately by NPC role (supplies by the quartermaster, training gear by the marshal, herbs by the healer, study desk by the arcane trainers, cookware by the cook), paths carved so lanes stay open, and 0 NPC-on-prop / 0 NPC-on-blocked-tile overlaps. The ONE genuine residual: the V0.20.8 pass fixed the Brann/merchant EXACT overlap but two east-ring quest NPCs still sat ~1 tile from a trainer (road_warden 1.41 from fighter_trainer; deepwood_surveyor 1.00 from rogue_trainer) - too close for Item 2's own rule, 'enough surrounding space for nameplates and interaction prompts to remain readable'. FIX: each moves one tile onto a prop-free camp tile that opens >=2.0 tiles from every other NPC (road_warden 109,97->110,97; deepwood_surveyor 109,103->109,102), verified by a proximity harness (2 tight pairs -> 0) and confirmed prop-free/walkable against the live object map. No props touched, no paths changed. Honest note: this was a small completion, not a rebuild - the heavy lifting was V0.20.8, and I say so rather than dress up two coordinate edits as an overhaul. Suite PASS, items 396/396, 0 console errors. See docs/V0.20.43_DEAD_LANTERN_CAMP.md.
