// V0.20.41: ARMOR PROFICIENCY - Roadmap Item 8 (Unified Skill Progression), first slice. The MECHANIC of four armor-proficiency skills (cloth/leather/chain/plate, level 1-20) that grow from taking real enemy hits while wearing that armour and raise the armour DR those pieces give. Built on existing conventions: data on the GAME (game.armorProficiency, like all belongings per V0.20.2); the bonus added to the derived-stats aggregator in recalculatePlayerStats, so it flows through computePlayerDerived and is recomputed on every equip, never written to item base (the spec's requirement); XP hooked into damageEntity's player-took-enemy-damage branch; persisted in serializeCharacterState/applyCharacterState and reset in resetCharacterOwnedState. VERIFIED THROUGH THE REAL PATHS, and the verification caught two things I'd otherwise have shipped wrong: (a) I first measured player.defense, which did NOT change - because DEFENSE and ARMOR are SEPARATE stats and damage mitigation uses ARMOR (armorReductionFor), not defense; measuring armor showed the bonus lands (+4 on Stalker leather, 23->27). (b) A flat 'damage taken 37' at both levels was the V0.20.27 one-shot cap masking the small delta - measuring armorReductionFor directly proved the mechanical benefit: leather DR 22.2%->24.6% at L20, high-armour gear 53.7%->56.2%. Full loop confirmed: XP gain, leveling 1-20, anti-exploit (trivial-damage floor + 1.5s cooldown), max-level cap, armour-DR bonus via the real recompute, save/load round-trip (level 12 preserved). HONEST GAPS, documented not hidden: (1) 44 STARTER armour items lack armorType (loot/shop/crafted gear all have it), so a brand-new character trains nothing until they equip real armour - tagging them needs a class->armour-weight mapping that neither the class defs nor the items encode yet (a design decision, not mine to invent 40 versions deep); (2) no dedicated skills-progress UI yet - the spec wants a progress display, which is the next slice. Suite PASS, items 396/396, 0 console errors. See docs/V0.20.41_ARMOR_PROFICIENCY.md.
