// V0.20.39: HIGH-CONTRAST TARGET RING - Roadmap Item 20 (accessibility), 4th of 12. AND an honest finding on the one I did NOT build: UI/FONT SCALING - the highest-value remaining accessibility item - is NOT a clean toggle here. The HUD is 165 hardcoded px font-sizes across 105 independently-positioned panels with no --ui-scale variable and no single wrapping container, so scaling it means a px->rem refactor or a per-panel zoom, i.e. a real multi-version refactor, not a pref. Reported rather than half-built. WHAT I DID build: high-contrast target reticle. drawActiveTargetIndicator (one clean function) now reads a highContrastTarget pref (off by default, its own Accessibility row, persisted) and, when ON, draws the current-target ring at 1.8x line width, full opacity, in pure BLACK backing + WHITE ring + white ticks instead of the thin translucent amber - so a low-vision player can always tell which enemy is selected. Only the indicator's look changes; targeting itself is untouched. VERIFIED by capturing the real stroke params: OFF main ring amber #ffe56d lw3 alpha0.96; ON white #ffffff lw5.4 alpha1 over a black #000000 backing. Off by default so no one who did not ask sees a change. Suite PASS, items 396/396, 0 console errors. Item 20 now 4/12. See docs/V0.20.39_HIGH_CONTRAST_TARGET.md.
