// V0.20.38: COLOURBLIND STATUS MARKERS - Roadmap Item 20 (accessibility), 3rd of 12. The spec's 'avoid colour-only status'. Audit first: status effects were ALREADY mostly colourblind-safe - every family renders a distinct GLYPH always (poison skull, frost flake, heal cross, ward square), the player's buffs and debuffs sit in SEPARATE trays (positional), and every pip has an aria-label ('Buff:'/'Debuff:'). The one real colour-reliant gap: on a MIXED tray (a target's effects), buff vs debuff VALENCE is both round pips distinguished mainly by colour, and a few glyphs collide (a 4-point star is shared by curse/stun/mana). FIX - an opt-in colorblindStatusMarkers pref (off by default, its own Accessibility row, persisted via uiPrefs) that adds a SHAPE valence marker to each pip: up-triangle for a buff, down-triangle for a debuff, top-left corner with a dark outline so it reads over any pip colour. renderTray reads the live pref (trays re-render each tick, so toggling is instant) and injects the marker; the family glyphs and aria-labels are untouched and always on. VERIFIED: pref in defaults; OFF = no markers, glyphs still present, pips unchanged; ON = buff->up-triangle, debuff->down-triangle, glyphs + aria-labels still present; a screenshot shows the markers on the HUD pips. Off by default so no one who did not ask sees a change. Suite PASS, items 396/396, 0 console errors. Item 20 now 3/12. See docs/V0.20.38_COLORBLIND_STATUS_MARKERS.md.
