// V0.20.37: REDUCE MOTION - Roadmap Item 20 (accessibility), the 2nd of 12 features, extending the screen-shake toggle (V0.20.19). A single reduceMotion pref (off by default, its own row in the Accessibility settings section, persisted through uiPrefs) that, when ON: (1) ZEROES screen shake - it is a superset of reduceScreenShake at the same one consumer gate in getCameraProjectionCache; (2) THINS decorative particle density by half via effectQualityScale (the single funnel every mote/spark/wisp count already passes through). THE SPEC'S HARD CONSTRAINT - 'preserve gameplay timing and information' - is honoured by construction: it only touches the COUNT of decorative particles and the screen shake, never an effect's lifetime, radius, damage timing or existence, so every ring, bolt, telegraph and health bar still draws exactly as before - there is just less swirling motion and no camera shake. VERIFIED through the real gates: pref present in defaults; effectQualityScale 1.0 -> 0.5 with the pref; a camera shake of 5 consumed as 5 normally and 0 under reduceMotion; a gameplay ring STILL spawns/draws with reduceMotion on (not removed); the toggle persists to localStorage. Off by default because a default must never silently change how the game looks for someone who did not ask. Suite PASS, items 396/396, 0 console errors. Item 20 now 2/12 (screen shake + reduced motion). See docs/V0.20.37_REDUCE_MOTION.md.
