// V0.20.36: ONE CAST SOUND, THE RIGHT ONE - a same-day fix of my own V0.20.35 bug, found by continuing the audio audit onto the ENEMY side. Checking enemy audio revealed spawnCastCue (the shared cast-cue funnel, called in the player cast pipeline at spell-system.js 2479/2648 AND by enemies/bots/mercs) ALREADY plays magic_cast. My V0.20.35 direct-resolveClassSpell test bypassed that pipeline, so I saw 'silent' and added a SECOND cast sound in resolveClassSpell - which meant the real instant-cast flow played magic_cast (cue) + my sound: for a magic spell the same id deduped, but for LIGHTNING it was magic_cast + thunder_roll and for MELEE magic_cast + attack_slash - a genuine DOUBLE cast sound (playSfx only dedupes identical ids within the cooldown). Verified the double empirically (real flow: magic_cast + thunder_roll + hit_thud). FIX - unify on the ONE real funnel: spawnCastCue now takes an options.sfx override (default magic_cast, so enemy/bot/merc callers are unchanged), the two player cast paths pass spellCastSfxId(spell), and the V0.20.35 resolveClassSpell sound is REMOVED. Result is not just de-duped but BETTER than V0.20.35: the kind-aware cast sound now fires in BOTH cast paths (cast-time and instant), where the removed line only covered instant. VERIFIED: Lightning Spark -> thunder_roll only (no magic_cast double), Fireball -> magic_cast, Cleave -> attack_slash, Mesmerize -> magic_cast, each exactly ONE cast sound + its impact; enemy cue still defaults to magic_cast. resolveClassSpell stays silent, which is correct for item-proc/bot callers that never showed a cue. Suite PASS, items 396/396, 0 console errors. See docs/V0.20.36_CAST_SOUND_DEDUP.md.
