// V0.20.35: SPELLS THAT MAKE A SOUND - Roadmap Item 18 (audio), first pass. The spells now LOOK distinct (V0.20.21-29) but cast in near-silence: measured, only 3 playSfx sites existed across ~280 spells (all pet summons), so a Fireball, a Cleave and a Mesmerize made no cast sound at all - bolts only played hit_thud on IMPACT, heals only chimed on the target. FIX at the same funnel that carries VFX identity - resolveClassSpell, which every class spell passes through - now plays a cast SOUND chosen by element/kind from the EXISTING SFX manifest (verified the .wav assets exist): thunder_roll for lightning/storm, attack_slash for melee/physical, magic_cast for everything else. Impact sounds (hit_thud on bolts, heal_chime on heals) are separate and UNTOUCHED - no doubling. Slight random pitch (rate 0.94-1.06) and an 0.08s cooldown so rapid casts do not sound robotic or spam. VERIFIED: Fireball magic_cast+hit_thud (was silent), Lightning Spark thunder_roll+hit_thud (element-appropriate), Cleave attack_slash+hit_thud (was silent), Mesmerize magic_cast (was silent), Minor Heal magic_cast+heal_chime (both, no double); selector maps lightning->thunder, melee->slash, fire/frost/arcane/heal->magic_cast. Suite PASS, items 396/396, 0 console errors. HONEST LIMIT: the manifest has no per-element cast assets (no fire/frost/arcane .wav), so those share magic_cast - full elemental audio would need new sound files, which I cannot author. See docs/V0.20.35_SPELL_CAST_AUDIO.md.
