// V0.20.34: BOSSES GET DESPERATE - Roadmap Item 19 CLOSED. The last gap - enrage conditions + distinct boss phases (no system existed, only 2 ad-hoc HP-threshold behaviours) - now built to the user's chosen design. SOFT ENRAGE: after a 45s grace, a boss's damage climbs +8% every 10s, capped at +80% - rising pressure that punishes stalling, no instant wipe. HP PHASES: at 50% HP +12% damage / +20% attack speed ('grows enraged'), at 25% +24% / +40% ('turns desperate') plus a ONE-TIME burst - summon adds if the boss has a summon ability, else a big telegraphed Desperate Strike (which reuses the enemy_aoe queue, so it is dodgeable AND interruptible like every other ground AoE). Built at one funnel: updateBossEscalation (called each frame from update()) recomputes _bossDamageMult and _bossAttackSpeedMult from combat time + current HP, so a healed boss de-escalates; the phase ANNOUNCE and the 25% burst are one-time high-water latches. Damage multiplier consumed in getEnemyAutoAttackRawDamage AND scaleEnemyAbilityDamage (covers auto-attacks, data abilities, string abilities, DoTs); attack-speed divides the swing delay at both assignment sites. Gated to bosses/minibosses/named (isBossEnemy) - normal and elite mobs never escalate (multiplier stays 1). Resets on respawn and on leash/deaggro (fresh fight). VERIFIED exactly: soft ramp 1.0@45s -> 1.08@55s -> 1.8@145s(capped); phases 50% 1.12/1.2, 25% 1.24/1.4; combined soft+phase 2.232; burst fires ONCE (1 telegraph + 1 queued Desperate Strike, no re-fire); the ability scaler scales exactly 1.5x under a 1.5 mult; a non-boss at 25% HP with 999s combat time stays 1/1; phase logs 'grows enraged'/'turns desperate' fire once each. Suite PASS, items 396/396, 0 console errors. ITEM 19 IS COMPLETE: CC resistance, telegraphs, one-shot cap, interrupts, and now enrage+phases - plus ability variety / threat / pack behaviour confirmed already-present. See docs/V0.20.34_BOSS_ENRAGE_PHASES.md.
