// V0.20.33: STUN IT AND THE FIRE NEVER FALLS - Roadmap Item 19 (interrupt opportunities), the natural join of the CC work (V0.20.27/30) and the telegraph work (V0.20.31/32). A telegraphed enemy ground-AoE now has a 0.5s window that is BOTH a dodge window and an INTERRUPT window: if the caster is hard crowd-controlled when the strike comes due, the strike is INTERRUPTED and never lands. Implemented at the one point every telegraphed strike resolves (the enemy_aoe case in updatePendingSpellImpacts): if the source has an active control buff tagged stun/silence/freeze/sleep/knockback/interrupt (INTERRUPT_CC_TAGS - NOT root or slow, a rooted caster can still finish its cast), the strike is cancelled and logged 'X's attack is interrupted!'. A caster that merely DIED still commits (V0.20.31 unchanged - the ground effect was already loosed); only a deliberate interrupt cancels. This makes every player stun a real interrupt tool, and rewards the CC-resistance tiers from V0.20.30 (a boss resists so its stun window is shorter, but landing one still stops the attack). VERIFIED: stun/silence/freeze interrupt (0 damage), root/slow/expired-stun do NOT (damage lands); end-to-end, an enemy telegraphs -> player stuns in the window -> AoE interrupted, while the same cast with no stun lands. Suite PASS, items 396/396, 0 console errors. See docs/V0.20.33_INTERRUPT_OPPORTUNITIES.md.
