// V0.20.32: EVERY GROUND AOE NOW WARNS - Roadmap Item 19, the bounded follow-up promised by V0.20.31. That version telegraphed the DATA-DRIVEN enemy AoE (executeDataAbility); this closes the gap for the older STRING-format abilities on the Ashroot Horror miniboss - ash_cloud, death_bloom, blightwood_pulse - which still applied their damage/status INSTANTLY via a centerTargets loop. All three now route through the SAME telegraph pattern (a shared telegraphAoe helper in tryAshrootHorrorAbility): a bossGroundTelegraph danger marker appears, then the strike lands 0.5s later on the enemy_aoe pending-impact queue - ash_cloud and death_bloom carry damage + their debuff (Ashen / Withered), blightwood_pulse is status-only (Blightwood Vulnerability). ashroot_crush (a melee crush at the target) and cinderroot_snare (a single-target snare) stay as they were. The now-unused centerTargets local was removed; its helper ashrootHostileTargets is left in place (a named module fn, now unreferenced - a noted follow-up cleanup, not removed to keep this change surgical). VERIFIED on a real ashroot enemy: all three fire, 0 instant damage at cast, 1 danger marker each, queued enemy_aoe (ash_cloud/death_bloom damage+status, blightwood status-only), and the damage lands after the 0.6s window. Suite PASS, 0 console errors. ALSO INVESTIGATED (thread 2): enrage conditions and boss phases. FINDING - there is NO general enrage or boss-phase system: 0 enrage fields authored anywhere, and every 'phase' reference in code is unrelated (entity living/dead, the silk boss WALK-IN entrance animation, fishing/portal state, decoration scatter). Only ad-hoc per-enemy HP-threshold behaviours exist (Ashroot heals at 48% HP). 'Distinct phases' and 'enrage conditions' are a FEATURE BUILD + design decisions, not a dead-field fix - reported for the user rather than speculatively built. See docs/V0.20.32_STRING_ABILITY_TELEGRAPHS.md.
