// V0.20.31: STEP OUT OF THE FIRE - Roadmap Item 19 (telegraph readability), the user chose a 0.5s window. Regular enemy ground-AoE abilities (executeDataAbility kinds aoe/venom_rain/silk_lines/poison_cloud/snare - ~20 abilities across 35 enemies) spawned their ring and dealt the damage on the SAME FRAME: zero reaction window, an unavoidable hit, exactly what the spec forbids ('clear telegraphs', 'dangerous without relying on unavoidable one-shot attacks'). Silk Web bosses already telegraph (V0.18.42) but the data-driven ability path did not. FIX, reusing existing infrastructure not new systems: a bossGroundTelegraph danger marker (its draw is generic; sized ringPx/5.8 so its circle matches the ability's blast) appears at the target, and the strike is queued on the EXISTING pending-impact queue (queuePendingSpellImpact, what the player's Meteorfall uses; already ticked each frame at game.js:2766) to land 0.5s later via a new 'enemy_aoe' kind that calls enemyAoeDamage/enemyAoeStatus. Damage is SNAPSHOTTED at cast; the strike is committed (lands even if the caster dies in the window). CLEAVE stays instant - it is a swing at the enemy's own body, not a ground effect. VERIFIED through the real path: at cast 0 instant damage + 1 telegraph + 1 queued (kind enemy_aoe, delay 0.5, damage 22 snapshotted); at 0.3s still 0; at 0.6s the strike lands at the target with the snapshot. Cleave: instant, 0 queued. Snare: status only, applied after the window. Poison_cloud: damage + DoT after the window. A screenshot shows the ground danger marker rendering. Suite PASS, items 396/396, 0 console errors. NOTE: the older STRING-format abilities (ash_cloud, death_bloom, blightwood_pulse on specific minibosses) are a separate code path and still instant - a bounded follow-up. See docs/V0.20.31_ENEMY_AOE_TELEGRAPHS.md.
