// V0.20.30: TWO PENDING CALLS, RESOLVED - the user chose the numbers, I wired them. (1) BOSS CC RESISTANCE: the V0.20.27 gate shipped but no enemy used it. Now controlResistanceOf falls back to a TIER default when a target has no explicit value - dungeonBoss 0.55, dungeonMiniBoss 0.40, elite 0.20, normal 0 (the user's 'Moderate' pick) - applied at the ONE funnel (baseControlResistance) rather than editing 28+ enemy data entries. An explicit data controlResistancePct still WINS, so any single enemy is tunable. Players carry none of these flags so their base stays 0 and only their buffs contribute - V0.20.27 unchanged. VERIFIED: a 3.2s stun becomes 1.44s on a boss, 1.92 miniboss, 2.56 elite, 3.2 normal; rank:'boss' string also triggers it; an explicit 0.1 on a boss overrides to 2.88; the player stays 3.2 and their 0.5 resist buff still gives 1.6. (2) CHANNEL TOOLTIPS: 7 spells claimed to 'channel for N seconds' but resolve INSTANTLY (no channel state exists in the engine - verified in the earlier audit). Reworded all 7 to describe the real instant multi-hit: Whirlwind Cleave 'Spin a two-handed weapon in place, striking nearby enemies three times at once', the rogue flurry 'Land five rapid dagger strikes at once', the ranger volley, arcane missiles ('Launch'), Spellstorm, the shadow drain ('Tear five pulses'), and Moonlit Tranquility ('Release a wave of lunar healing' - phrased to stay accurate whether it heals instantly or via a HoT). Zero 'channel' claims remain in any spell description; the dead channelDuration/channelTime fields were left in place (harmless, and preserve the aspiration if channeling is ever built). Suite PASS, items 396/396, 0 dialogue issues, 0 console errors. See docs/V0.20.30_CC_RESIST_AND_CHANNEL_TOOLTIPS.md.
