// V0.20.29: EVERY CLASS NOW HAS A FACE - Roadmap Item 6, the caster bespoke pass COMPLETE. The five palette-only casters (Druid, Shaman, Summoner, Enchanter, Ranger) each get a bespoke burst, built as ONE shared isolated effect type (casterMotif) keyed by MOTIF so five classes reuse one draw path instead of five near-duplicates - same isolation discipline as the Wizard's V0.20.28, nothing shared with vfxStyle. Motifs, derived from each class's own school/damageType/tags and NEVER buff.color: Druid nature (green leaves) / lunar (pale-violet moon glow); Shaman storm (teal arcs) / earth (amber shards) / spirit (wisps); Summoner planar (violet rift); Enchanter mind (rose psychic pulses - and it fires on CONTROL too, not just damage, since the Enchanter is a control class); Ranger hunt (moss crosshair + streaks). Wired at each resolver's single damage helper (Shaman hit, Druid damageEnemy, Enchanter hitEnemy + applyControl, Summoner damage, Ranger both damage sites) so one edit per class covers all its spells. VERIFIED: all 8 motions draw without throwing and are safe at radius 0 (every canvas radius clamped >= 1, the negative-radius black-screen guard); motif resolution correct per class (Lightning Spark->storm, Stone Shard->earth, Spirit Flame->spirit, Thorn Whip->nature, Moonfire->lunar, Planar Bolt->planar, Mind Spark & Mesmerize->mind, Steady Shot & Volley->hunt); a screenshot shows the eight motifs rendering as distinct colours and shapes; 0 console errors. ALL 14 CLASSES NOW HAVE BESPOKE VFX: Assassin/Cleric/Necromancer/Bard (full bespoke), Fighter/Rogue/Paladin/Warden (melee silhouettes), Wizard (elemental), and these five. See docs/V0.20.29_CASTER_MOTIF_VFX.md.
