// V0.20.28: THE WIZARD'S ELEMENTS FINALLY LOOK DIFFERENT - Roadmap Item 6, the bespoke pass begins on the six palette-only casters. The Wizard is the class whose whole identity is elemental force, and every one of its spells drew the SAME wizard-blue rune ring: a Fireball, a Frost Nova and an Arcane Bolt were visually identical. Palette identity (V0.20.21) made the Wizard look distinct from a Necromancer, but did nothing WITHIN the Wizard - fire, frost and arcane all resolved to sourceClass=wizard -> rune/blue. This adds a bespoke elemental burst: drawWizardElementEffect, an ISOLATED effect type (nothing else spawns it) so it differentiates fire/frost/lightning/arcane without touching the shared vfxStyle palette the other 13 classes depend on. Fire is an orange bloom with rising embers, frost a cyan ring throwing ice shards, lightning yellow crackling arcs, arcane a violet rune geometry. Element is derived from damageType + tags + id, NEVER from buff.color (Ignite ships the wizard's blue - the same lie the DoT plume caught in V0.20.25). Wired into the Wizard's 10 damage spells - AoE bursts at the center (keeping V0.20.23's accurate area ring underneath), single-target bursts at the target (keeping the bolt). VERIFIED: element resolution correct on all 10 (Fireball/Flame Wave/Ignite -> fire, Frost Nova/Frost Lance/Ice Prison/Shatter -> frost, Arcane Bolt/Barrage/Mana Spear -> arcane); all four element branches draw without throwing; zero-radius is safe (every canvas radius clamped >= 1, the negative-radius black-screen guard); a screenshot shows the orange fire and cyan frost bursts side by side, clearly distinct. Suite PASS, 0 console errors. FIVE casters still to go - Druid, Shaman, Summoner, Enchanter, Ranger. See docs/V0.20.28_WIZARD_ELEMENTAL_VFX.md.
