// V0.20.27: THE RESIST THAT NEVER RESISTED - Roadmap Item 19 (crowd-control resistance), and my FIRST step into enemy/boss combat. controlResistancePct was authored on THREE player defensive buffs - Unstoppable Footwork (0.5), Spirit Walk (0.3), Blink (0.2) - each promising to shrug off roots and stuns. It was TRIPLY dead: authored, then STRIPPED by normalizeEffect (not in its field whitelist, so the stored buff never even carried it), and read in ZERO places. A player popped Unstoppable Footwork before a pull and it did literally nothing. Verified exhaustively: 6 occurrences codebase-wide, all authoring, 0 reads. THE FIX is the missing CENTRAL gate, at StatusEffects.applyToEntity - the one point every status effect passes through (the same funnel Item 13's effect policy uses). (1) normalizeEffect now preserves controlResistancePct so the buff carries it. (2) applyToEntity, when the incoming effect IS a control (typed 'control' OR carrying a stun/root/silence/slow tag), scales its duration by (1 - the target's aggregate controlResistancePct), summed from the target's active buffs plus an optional base field on the entity/baseType, capped at 0.9 so resistance SHORTENS control but never fully immunizes through this path. Non-control effects untouched. VERIFIED end to end: field survives normalization; a 3.2s root becomes 1.6s under Unstoppable Footwork, 2.24s under Spirit Walk, 2.56s under Blink - the three buffs work for the first time; stacked resist 0.8 -> 0.64s; a DoT applied under a 0.5 resist buff stays a full 10s (resistance touches ONLY control); an unresisted target keeps the full 3.2s. SCOPE, HONEST: this fixes the dead field and makes PLAYER control-resistance real, and it BUILDS the gate Item 19's enemy-side CC resistance needs - applyToEntity already reads baseType.controlResistancePct, so a boss becomes CC-resistant the moment its data carries one field. I did NOT invent boss resistance values - that is a balance decision left with the user, exactly like the channel tooltips. Suite PASS, 0 console errors. See docs/V0.20.27_CONTROL_RESISTANCE.md.
