// V0.20.26: BOLTS LEAVE THE HAND, NOT THE BELLY - Roadmap Item 6 fidelity, the spec's 'a projectile must originate from the correct casting hand'. AND IT OPENS BY CORRECTING MY OWN ESTIMATE: I told the user this was a 14-renderer, all-or-nothing build and the lowest-value option. MEASURING KILLED THAT CLAIM - every humanoid, across BOTH the class-identity path and the humanoid-base path, publishes its feet (_lastGroundAnchor) and head (_nameplateAnchor) IDENTICALLY (feet ~633, head ~535, body ~97px, dead uniform across Wizard/Necromancer/Cleric/Druid/Ranger), and the bolt origin sat at ~37-55% up the body - the BELLY - lifted a FIXED 24px that ignored body height. So the cast-height fix is ONE uniform change in the bolt path, not fourteen: spawnBolt now derives originLift from the caster's own feet/head span (cast point ~62% up = chest/hand height), and drawHighQualityBoltEffect lifts the SOURCE by it instead of the hardcoded 24. Scale-correct (uses the real on-screen body height, so a 1.5x enemy scales too), camera-safe (a px lift on the re-projected source each frame, exactly like the 24 it replaces), and it falls back to 24 for any caller with no anchors (verified). Only the SOURCE moves - target/tip stay on the enemy's body, so aim is unchanged. Verified: all four caster classes now originate at a consistent 62% up (was an INCONSISTENT 37-55% depending on each bolt's height option); no-anchor fallback keeps 24; a blue bolt visibly leaves the wizard's upper body in a live screenshot. HONEST SCOPE: this fixes origin HEIGHT and makes it uniform; the exact per-class hand-SIDE horizontal offset (the cast hand sits ~16px to one side in the rig, facing-dependent) remains a larger per-renderer refinement and is NOT claimed here. Assassin projectile untouched (its own spawner, no originLift). Suite PASS, 0 console errors. See docs/V0.20.26_BOLT_ORIGIN_HEIGHT.md.
