// V0.20.25: A POISON YOU CAN SEE WHILE IT KILLS YOU - Roadmap Item 6 fidelity, the spec's other named case 'a damage-over-time effect must persist while the debuff is active'. Same missing per-frame buff pass V0.20.24 built for shields; this extends it to DoTs. isDotDebuff keys on the DEFINITION (hostile + periodicDamage > 0 + remaining > 0), not the 'dot' type string some periodic debuffs omit. THE FINDING THAT SHAPED IT: buff.color does NOT encode the element - ground-truthed against real casts, Ignite (fire) ships the WIZARD'S BLUE #6fa8ff and Bleeding Vein (bleed) ships grey #cfd4d9 - so a fire DoT tinted by buff.color would read as frost. The spec requires the visual to communicate DAMAGE TYPE, which is the one field buff.color gets wrong, so dotElementColor derives from damageType then tags and NEVER from buff.color: verified Ignite renders ORANGE #ff7a3d not blue. THE DEFERRAL CONCERN, MEASURED AND DISSOLVED: DoTs are on nearly every enemy in a fight, so the worry was clutter and cost. Clutter - every DoT on an actor MERGES into ONE plume tinted by the strongest (a 5-DoT enemy shows one affliction, not five), motes capped at 4. Cost - measured 3.83us per fully-afflicted actor, 0.01us to early-exit an unafflicted one, 0.11ms/frame for THIRTY fully-afflicted enemies (0.7% of a 60fps budget). The plume is a faint element-coloured ground taint plus up to 4 small rising motes, mote count scaling with total dps (the spec's 'Power' cue); cheap - one ellipse + <=4 arc fills, no gradients. No fade-IN (DoTs are short and want instant combat feedback); fades OUT only in the final 0.6s so expiry reads. VERIFIED with the aged-buff + failing-negative-control discipline: real DoTs draw 2-4 motes, a friendly HoT / an expired DoT / an empty buff list each draw 0 (controls that CAN fail); shield and DoT coexist on one actor; and through the LIVE loop - 368 player-plume draws while afflicted, 0 the instant the DoT was removed, renderer restored clean. Suite PASS, 0 console errors. See docs/V0.20.25_DOT_PERSISTENCE.md.
