// V0.20.24: A SHIELD YOU CAN SEE FOR AS LONG AS IT PROTECTS - Roadmap Item 6 fidelity, the spec's example 'a shield must remain visible for the actual protection duration'. It was not: a shield fired a ~0.68s cast flash and then NOTHING - Guardian Aura lasts 1800s and was visible for 0.68 of them - because the entity renderer had NO per-frame pass over active buffs at all (confirmed: entity-renderer.js drew from statusEffects zero times; the only buff visuals were sub-second spawnStatusPulse flashes). BUILT that pass: drawEntityStatusAuras(e), called from drawEntity AFTER the body so the aura envelops without occluding. It is driven STRAIGHT OFF actor.buffs, so an aura's VISUAL lifetime IS the buff's gameplay lifetime - it appears the frame the buff is applied and vanishes the frame remaining hits 0, because there is no second lifetime that could drift. Verified through the LIVE render loop, not a manual call: 218 player-aura draws in ~1s while shielded, then 0 the instant the shield was removed. Scoped to PROTECTIVE buffs only (the spec's named category) via isProtectiveBuff: tags shield/ward/aura/barrier/bulwark/absorb/guard/etc, OR absorbRemaining>0, OR damageTakenMultiplier in (0,1) - the last arm is what catches Guardian Aura, whose only tag is 'aura'. Ground-truthed against real casts first: Shield of Faith (dtm 0.85, tags shield/ward), Guardian Aura (dtm 0.97, tag aura), Radiant Bulwark and Mana Shield (absorbRemaining 156/108) - all detected; a haste buff, a hostile DoT and an empty buff list all correctly draw NOTHING (negative controls that CAN fail: 0 ellipses each). One dome even when shields stack (2 shields -> 3 ellipses, not 6). A NEAR-MISS caught by testing: age = duration - remaining, so a freshly-cast buff has age 0 -> fadeIn 0 -> invisible, and my first test FROZE time so age stayed 0 and every case drew 0 ellipses - the shields AND the negative controls, a vacuous pass. Re-run with the buff aged past the 0.3s fade-in, the shields drew and the controls stayed 0. The fade-in is intentional (the shield forms as the cast flash fades); a save loaded mid-duration has age>0 and shows instantly. Also draws for ALLY bots (Calia's Guardian Aura got a dome), correctly - the predicate keys on the buff, not the actor kind. DoTs are the same mechanism and the spec's other named case, but they are ubiquitous in combat and want a clutter/perf pass of their own, so they are deliberately NOT drawn yet. Suite PASS, 0 console errors, live renderer restored clean after instrumentation. See docs/V0.20.24_PERSISTENT_SHIELD_AURA.md.
//
// V0.20.23: THE BLAST YOU SEE IS THE BLAST THAT HITS YOU - Roadmap Item 6 fidelity, the spec's own example: 'a ground-targeted spell must show the correct affected area'. It did not. spawnRing's radius argument is SCREEN PIXELS (the || 18 default proves the intent), but resolvers passed spell.radius, which is WORLD TILES - two units in one expression. MEASURED, not reasoned: one world radius projects to 73.54px on x, so Meteorfall's 7-tile blast (515px of real damage) drew a ring peaking at 46px. ELEVEN TIMES too small. Fireball 3 tiles/179px drew 20px; Flame Wave 4 tiles drew 20px. The game has been killing players ~11x further out than the graphic showed, and no player could learn a spell's true reach by looking - the identical bug the V0.19.x cone fix addressed, still alive for rings. FIXED AT THE FUNNEL, not the ~99 call sites: resolveClassSpell already publishes the caster, so it now also publishes the AREA radius, and spawnRing carries it as an optional effect.worldRadius. THE TRAP THE DATA REVEALED: spell.radius does NOT mean one thing - on an aoe kind it is the blast, on a BUFF it is the ALLY SEARCH range (Mana Shield authors radius 14), so a blanket conversion would have ringed the caster in an 834px halo. Published for aoe/aoeDebuff/aoeHeal/aoeMelee ONLY; verified 0 buff rings leaked. The renderer sizes from the REAL projection via worldRingMetrics (a ground circle's rightmost point is world (R/root2,-R/root2); a 360-sample sweep agrees to 2dp), which also exposed that the engine's true y:x ratio is 0.558 while the stylised ring hardcodes 0.42 - so an area ring was the wrong SHAPE too. World rings use the true ratio; legacy pixel callers keep 0.42 untouched. AND THE SIZING TARGET IS THE PEAK, NOT p=1: easeOutBack OVERSHOOTS to ~1.1, so r peaks at base*2.098 rather than base*1.96 - sizing to p=1 would let the graphic claim ~7% MORE reach than the spell damages. Sized to the peak, it may under-draw for an instant but never over-promises. ringPeakMult() measures that from the live easing rather than hardcoding it, so changing easeOutBack cannot silently desynchronise the drawing from the damage. MY FIRST VERIFICATION WAS TAUTOLOGICAL - it computed (truePx / ringPeakMult()) * ringPeakMult() and asserted it equalled truePx, which it does by algebra: a check that CANNOT fail, the 4th vacuous probe of this session. Re-done by instrumenting drawExpandingRing and driving the effect across its whole life through the real draw path: Meteorfall's widest drawn ring 46px -> 515px, exactly its damage edge, overshoot false, renderer restored after. Real results that survived: 37 area rings across all 14 classes sized from world space, 0 buff rings wrongly sized, 0 area spells spawning multiple rings (the funnel's real risk, checked not assumed). See docs/V0.20.23_AOE_AREA_FIDELITY.md.
//
// V0.20.22: FOUR CLASSES WITH NO FACE - Roadmap Item 6, closing the caster half. V0.20.21 made the palettes reachable and I REPORTED THAT EIGHT CLASSES GAINED AN IDENTITY. That was FALSE and I never checked it before writing it: Shaman, Summoner, Enchanter and Ranger match NO regex in vfxStyle and still resolved to the generic default - there was nothing for the wiring to reach. The user delegated the design call, so this AUTHORS the four missing palettes: shaman storm-teal #5fd8e0 / totem-amber #ffd98a, motion 'wisp' (spirit smoke); summoner planar violet #9d7dff, motion 'rune' (conjuring circles); enchanter mesmeric rose #ff8fd0, motion 'wave' (arc sigils); ranger moss #a8d86a / leather #d9b378, motion 'precise'. Motions REUSE existing draw branches - nothing new was invented, and 'precise' has no ring/pulse branch, so the Ranger gets colours only: reported, not dressed up. PLACEMENT WAS THE ENTIRE FIX AND ONLY THE REAL SPELL NAMES REVEALED IT: vfxStyle tests IN ORDER, and the Shaman casts Lightning Spark / Stormcall / Chain Storm / Ghostfire (all -> the WIZARD line), the Summoner casts Arcane Spark / Soul Link / Elemental Rotation ('Rotation' starts with 'rot', so even V0.20.21's \brot claims it for NECRO), the Enchanter casts Arcane Binding / Glyphstorm. Placed below those lines, the Shaman's whole storm identity would render wizard-blue and the class terms would never fire - the warden shadow bug of V0.20.21, this time authored by me. So the four lines go HIGH, above necro/wizard/cleric, but deliberately BELOW the poison and blade lines, which name an EFFECT rather than a caster and should still win. \b-anchored so 'summoner' is not claimed by 'Summon Familiar' nor 'ranger' by a stray 'stranger'. MY FIRST AUDIT WAS VACUOUS AGAIN: 280 spell names checked via spawnRing, 0 collisions - MEANINGLESS, because nothing sets effect.label on a ring (only spawnStatusPulse does), so the name never entered the key. Caught ONLY by a NEGATIVE CONTROL (necromancer casting 'Phantom Army', which MUST be stolen by the enchanter line) reporting canDetect:false. Re-run through spawnStatusPulse: 9 real collisions, NONE mine, ALL pre-existing - Fighter 'Bonebreaker' and Cleric 'Purify Soul' render as necromancy (bone/soul), Druid 'Barkskin Blessing' as holy, Druid 'Moonfire' as arcane; while Assassin 'Poison Dart' and Rogue 'Venom Edge' rendering as poison is the poison line working AS DESIGNED. All left alone rather than 'fixed' on a guess - they are judgment calls about intent, not obvious bugs. VERIFIED BY REAL CASTS, not by the file: Lightning Spark -> bolt:shaman:wisp (NOT wizard - placement proven), Arcane Spark -> bolt:summoner:rune, Mind Spark -> bolt:enchanter:wave, Steady Shot -> bolt:ranger:precise; 14/14 classes now resolve to a palette; 0 console errors. See docs/V0.20.22_FOUR_CLASS_PALETTES.md.
//
// V0.20.21: NOBODY TOLD THE RING WHO CAST IT - Roadmap Item 6, the caster half, and it began by RETRACTING MY OWN PREVIOUS REPORT. I told the user spell.projectile was 'double dead - authored zero times and passed under a key spawnBolt ignores'. BOTH HALVES WERE FALSE. The compiler GENERATES it (spell-compiler-system.js:192, projectileDescriptorFor, for bolt/boltDot/boltSummon/drain kinds), and spawnBolt DOES read it - twenty lines below the `style || kind` line I stopped reading at - to derive travelDuration. I grepped data/spells.js for the writer and the top of spawnBolt for the reader; the writer was in a third file and the reader was further down the same function. I have written 'don't ask whether the data is there, ask whether anything reads it' into four reports and then declared a live field dead without checking either end. THE REAL FIND, and it is the inverse of dead data - a system fully BUILT and UNREACHABLE: vfxStyle() (render/effects-renderer.js:90) keys a palette off `sourceClass + school + kind + style + label` and maps it to EIGHT school identities, each with its own secondary/dark/smoke and a `motion` - rune, wisp, bubble, bloom, organic, wave, precise, impact. drawHighQualityRingEffect branches on that motion into drawRuneFragments / drawSmokeWisps / drawArcSigil. All of it implemented. And of NINETY-NINE spawnRing calls in spell-system.js, exactly ONE passed any identity key - so the key resolved to ' bolt bolt ', matched no regex, fell to the generic default at line 100, and the Wizard's rune fragments have never been drawn. Not one caster class had a look because nothing ever told the effect who cast it. THE FIX IS THE FUNNEL, NOT THE CALL SITES: patching 99 sites is the cascade the golden rules forbid and 99 chances to miss the 100th. resolveClassSpell is the single dispatcher all 13 classes route through, so it now publishes the lowercased casting class into this._spellVfxSourceClass, and decorateEffectVisualPayload (which spawnRing already funnels through) falls back to it. One change; every existing call site fixed and every future one for free. Restores the prior value instead of clearing (a spell that resolves another spell must not strip the outer cast's identity) via try/finally (a throwing resolver must not leave the context stuck on). NOT defaulted from effect.sourceClass: effects are POOLED, and that would have inherited the previous caster's class - the identical reset hazard spawnBolt already documents for travelDuration. SCOPE CORRECTED A THIRD TIME: 'nine caster classes need this' was wrong - config.js:100 records that V0.18.31 already gave the Cleric bespoke holy VFX, as V0.18.29 did the Assassin. Explicit payload still beats the context, so both keep their designed looks; verified the Cleric draw functions never call vfxStyle at all (untouched), and the Assassin's dart/knife/crossbow kinds already match at lines 92-93 BEFORE any class regex, so sourceClass cannot displace them. The change is strictly additive: only effects that previously matched NOTHING now match their class. TURNING THE WIRE ON EXPOSED TWO SHADOWED TERMS, ONE LIVE IN THE SHIPPED GAME: vfxStyle tests its lines IN ORDER with UNANCHORED substrings, so an earlier line claims words meant for a later one. 'warden' is authored into the druid line but 'warden' CONTAINS 'ward', so the cleric line above claimed it - the Warden wore holy gold and that druid term has NEVER been reachable. And 'protect' is authored into the cleric line but 'pROTect' CONTAINS 'rot', so the necro line claimed it: because spawnStatusPulse sets label from the spell name and line 462 explicitly handles 'protect' labels, EVERY CLERIC PROTECTION SPELL HAS BEEN RENDERING AS NECROMANCY GREEN in the shipped game (that one predates me; 'warden' only became reachable this version). Both are drawRuneFragments again - authored, correct, unreachable, one line away. Fixed at the ROOT, the unanchored substring: ward -> ward(?!en) (keeps wards/warding, releases warden); rot -> \\brot, word-start only (keeps rot/rotting/rotten, releases protect). THEN AUDITED ALL 50 AUTHORED TERMS instead of fixing them one at a time: every term reaches the palette its own line intends, 0 shadowed, derived words (rotting/wards/warding/roots/fireball/snowstorm) all still correct. AND I OVER-CLAIMED THE SCOPE AGAIN IN MY OWN REPORT: I wrote that eight classes including Shaman, Summoner, Enchanter and Ranger 'now have a school identity'. FALSE, and unchecked before writing - those four match NO regex in vfxStyle and still resolve generic. Measured: fighter impact, rogue precise (NEW - joined the blade line, same silver-and-blood as the assassin), paladin bloom (NEW - every Paladin SPELL is holy; their martial identity is V0.20.20's melee silhouettes), warden organic (NEW - the shadow bug is why it never worked), assassin precise, cleric bloom, wizard rune, necromancer wisp, druid organic, bard wave; shaman/summoner/enchanter/ranger MAGIC = still generic. 10 of 14 have an identity, 4 do not, and giving those four one means AUTHORING NEW PALETTES - a design decision, not a wiring fix. THE FUNNEL WAS NOT ENOUGH, AND ONLY CASTING FOR REAL FOUND IT - I proved the wire in isolation and called it shipped; the user said 'make sure it actually works'. Booting a real Wizard exposed a hole at once: spawnStatusPulse (effects-system.js:472) sets its identity BY HAND and never calls decorateEffectVisualPayload, so Mana Shield drew runes on the ring and a GENERIC pulse on the player in the SAME cast. arcane_intellect HID IT: its pulse showed 'rune' not from the fix but because spawnStatusPulse sets effect.label and the name 'Arcane Intellect' matches /arcane/ BY ACCIDENT - one spell in three passing FOR THE WRONG REASON, which is how a partial fix survives review. Fixed there too; and spawnBolt was VERIFIED not assumed (sets sourceClass by hand at 373 but calls the decorator at 398, which overwrites, so bolts were already covered - assuming it would have been the 4th assumption bug of the session). REAL CASTS: Mana Shield/Blink -> statusPulse:wizard:rune + ring:wizard:rune; Arcane Bolt/Frost Lance -> bolt:wizard:rune; Ignite -> statusPulse:wizard:rune; Fireball/Frost Nova -> ring:wizard:rune. THE DEAD BRANCH NOW EXECUTES, counted not eyeballed: drawRuneFragments ran 0 times for generic rings (the bug reproduced) and 872 times for identical rings with a known caster; renderer restored afterwards, probe character never persisted. STILL GENERIC AND DELIBERATELY OUT OF SCOPE: combatImpact/combatSpark resolve to '-:magic' - spawned by the DAMAGE path, and drawCombatImpactEffect only branches on motion === 'impact', so pushing the caster's class in would hand a Wizard 'rune' (undrawable there) and change MELEE impacts as a side effect. Honestly still broken, and it hints that function's 'impact' smoke branch may be unreachable the same way - a separate finding, not a verified claim. VERIFIED AT RUNTIME, both halves of the wire: consumer - wizard->rune, necromancer->wisp, druid->organic, explicit cleric beats wizard context->bloom, and with no cast in flight a recycled effect resolves to '' not the last caster (pooling leak closed). Publisher - the dispatcher publishes 'wizard' from 'Wizard', passes the return value through, restores after, survives NESTED casts (inner necromancer, outer still wizard), and clears on THROW. AND MY FIRST SUITE PROBE WAS VACUOUS: it read r.statPipeline / r.dataIssues, which do not exist (the real shape is r.summary.*), so every '0 issues' was `undefined || []` and meant nothing - caught only because statPipeline printed 'undefined/undefined'. The real run: ok true, statPipeline 15/15, items 396/396, 0 data/economy/dialogue/spellShape issues, 0 compiler errors, warnings 2, 0 console errors. See docs/V0.20.21_CASTER_IDENTITY_FUNNEL.md.
