// V0.18.79: ROADMAP ITEM 10 (SAVE COMPATIBILITY & MIGRATION) - new content now reaches existing saves. ROOT CAUSE: systems/world-serializer.js serialize() snapshots every shipped-content catalog (items, spells, loot tables, recipes, quests, npcs, mobs, bosses, dungeons, puzzles, professions, stations, resource types) INTO the world save, and Game.prototype.autoSaveCharacterState() (systems/save-system.js) writes a world save to localStorage on the character-autosave timer. On boot game.js:606 loadSavedWorldState({duringBoot}) restored that snapshot verbatim (apply() used cloneObjectOr = saved-if-present-else-shipped), so content added in a newer build (the V0.18.75-78 belts/bags/chest/legs) was fully shadowed by the stale snapshot and never appeared for any player who had autosaved once. FIX (surgical, in the owning module): new helper mergeShippedCatalog(saved, shipped) = clone of Object.assign({}, shipped, saved) - overlays the CURRENT shipped catalog underneath the saved snapshot so every shipped id is present (new content appears) while any saved entry still WINS on id collision (editor edits and custom save-only ids preserved untouched). apply() now uses it for all 14 shipped-content catalogs instead of cloneObjectOr. Purely additive for new shipped ids: it never mutates or drops a saved entry, so it cannot regress an existing save or an editor customization. Zone PLACEMENTS (editorNpcs/editorMobSpawns/attributes/resources/events/dungeonMarkers/spawnPoints), runtime state (pending*RuntimeState), zoneProperties and classSpellSlots are untouched (still cloneObjectOr) - those are the player's world/progress, not shipped catalogs. Verified: node --check clean; JSON clean; 0 console errors; simulated a pre-legs stale save (0 legs in snapshot) -> after apply() editorItems has all 10 legs, all compile as slot legs; a saved item override still wins on collision; a custom save-only id is preserved (313 = 312 shipped + 1 custom). NOTE (out of scope, safe default): balance changes to an EXISTING shipped id and new drops added to a PRE-EXISTING loot table still do not retroactively override the saved copy (saved wins on collision); new items stay obtainable regardless because vendor stock reads the live DR.SHOP_ITEM_LISTS and new recipe ids merge in. A shipped-wins refresh would be a separate opt-in. See docs/V0.18.79_SAVE_MIGRATION.md.
