// V0.15.86: Phase 9 bank system - new systems/bank-system.js: 48-slot personal per-character storage (this.bank), now opened from the in-world Dead Lantern Stash chest instead of the Game Menu, deposit by clicking a bag item while Stash is open, withdraw by clicking a stored item, full save-system integration (systems/save-system.js) alongside inventory/equipment/bags. Deposit reuses the existing item drop-protection check rather than a new "canBank" flag.
// V0.15.85: Phase 8 class/stat/item parity (Intersect gaps identified in docs/PHASE_7_CLASS_STAT_INVENTORY_AUDIT.txt) - added an opt-in magicResist stat + magic-only mitigation path layered on top of (never replacing) the existing armor mitigation, and a 'true' damage type that bypasses all mitigation (core/stats.js, systems/combat-system.js); added opt-in per-class hpRegen/manaRegen stats wired into the existing passive regen loop (systems/combat-system.js); added an explicit item twoHanded flag (now set on the Blackroot Staff) consumed ahead of the pre-existing name-regex fallback; added opt-in item cooldownMs/cooldownGroup and castsSpellId (self/friendly spells only) to the consumable-use path (systems/item-compiler-system.js). Every addition defaults to fully inert (0/null) for all existing classes/items/content, verified by a full-project syntax sweep with zero errors - no existing combat, damage, or item-use behavior changes unless new content explicitly opts in.
// V0.15.84: Phase 6 map/layer/attribute/warp/resource/crafting parity + editor validation/overlay pass + patch notes correction. Fixed a bug where game.currentZone==='dungeon' had no branch in the layered map editor's zoneKey(), silently checking Dark Woods' painted Blocked/NPC Avoid data for dungeon tiles instead of correctly finding no data; added dungeon/puzzle descriptor cross-referencing to core/registry.js (bossIds/puzzleIds/lootTableId/keyItemId/caveZoneId); extended the existing editor validation report with warp-target validation (unknown zone/map, out-of-bounds, self-loop) and mob-spawn-on-blocked-tile/cave-entrance and resource-on-blocked-tile checks; added independent overlay visibility toggles for the previously always-on attribute/resource/event/npc/mob-spawn/dungeon marker categories in the F10 editor; fixed a pre-existing bug where the "Validate Only" button had no handler and did nothing; added self-loop prevention and a "Clear Layer" action to the F9 layered map editor. Also reconstructed and wired up in-game/launcher patch notes (previously stale since V0.15.78) covering every phase to date, and added PATCH_NOTES.md as a structured canonical reference. Full Intersect-style editor layout parity (map explorer tree, tabbed form inspector replacing window.prompt-based entity editing, per-layer opacity/reorder, ~10 new attribute types with no backing gameplay system) was scoped out this pass as a much larger, separate undertaking - see docs/PHASE_6_MAP_EDITOR_PATCH_NOTES.txt Known Limitations.
// V0.15.83: Phase 5 event/quest/condition/variable parity - added global event variables and per-event-instance self-switches (systems/event-system.js, both entirely new concepts, persisted through the existing save pipeline), a general condition evaluator (variable/selfSwitch/questAvailable/questCompleted/level/itemOwned) wired into the generic event command-list fallback (never the quest/dialogue/chest/shop/warp shortcuts, which are unaffected), new setVariable/setSelfSwitch event commands, an optional quest.requiredConditions gate reusing the same evaluator (systems/quest-system.js), optional NPC dialogueVariants (systems/npc-system.js), and fixed a real messaging bug where an event-system.js quest-hook duplicated quest-system.js's chooseQuestFromSource logic but was missing the "locked" (prerequisite/level not met) case, incorrectly telling players a locked quest was "already completed." No shipped event, quest, or NPC uses any of the new opt-in fields, so existing event/quest/dialogue behavior is unchanged except for that one bug fix - verified by 47 automated test cases run against the actual edited files.
// V0.15.82: Phase 4 NPC AI/spawn/leash/loot ownership - fixed a confirmed gap where mob spawn/roam validity (systems/mob-spawn-system.js isTileBlockedForZone) never consulted the Layered Map Editor's "Blocked"/"NPC Avoid" painted attributes (only its own separate legacy attribute store), so mobs could spawn/roam through tiles painted Blocked or NPC Avoid in the F9/F10 editor; added an optional per-mob data-driven flee-HP field (baseType.fleeHp, entities/enemy.js) replacing a hardcoded 0.18 ratio, defaulting to the same 0.18 for all current content; and enforced the existing (previously unenforced) party-loot eligibility tag in systems/loot-system.js so corpse loot correctly rejects non-eligible takers on genuine multi-member party kills while remaining a complete no-op for solo play. All three changes are backward compatible - verified by 31 automated test cases run against the actual edited files.
// V0.15.81: Phase 3 combat/spell/status/projectile parity - consolidated three duplicated hostile-target-resolution implementations in systems/spell-system.js into one shared systems/combat-system.js validator (Game.prototype.resolveHostileSpellTarget); added opt-in spell cooldown groups; wired up the previously-inert 'stun'/'silence' status tags to actually block casting/attacking and added a new 'invulnerable' damage-blocking tag (systems/status-effect-system.js, systems/combat-system.js, systems/spell-system.js); added the same hostile/stun validation to Game.prototype.tauntEnemy (systems/threat-system.js, which had none); added an opt-in projectile descriptor so bolt-kind spells can visually travel over distance/speed instead of an instant fixed-fade line (systems/spell-compiler-system.js, systems/effects-system.js, render/effects-renderer.js) without changing when damage is applied. All additions are backward compatible - no existing spell/status opts into the new fields, so current combat feel and balance are unchanged; this is confirmed by a 32-case automated regression test run against the actual edited files.
// V0.15.80: Phase 2 save/migration hardening and account/character gate safety - audited the login/account/character-select gate (confirmed already correctly blocking click/tap/key/gamepad bypass, no code change needed there) and added account/character save schema migration metadata + safe fallback paths (systems/save-system.js): schema-drift and dropped-character-slot events are now logged and recorded in a capped migrationHistory instead of failing silently.
